HEADWORD: Pessimist
<hw>Pes"si*mist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pessimus</ets> worst: cf. F. <ets>pessimiste</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Metaph.)</fld> <def>One who advocates the doctrine of
pessimism; -- opposed to <ant>optimist</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who looks on the dark side of things.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

